      • getImageUrl

        @Nonnull
public static java.lang.String getImageUrl​(long id,
                                           boolean isAlbum)
        Generate an image url from an image ID.

        The image ID 10 was chosen because it provides images wide up to 1200px (when the original image width is more than or equal this resolution).

        Other integer values are possible as well (e.g. 0 is a very large resolution, possibly the original); see IMAGE_URL_SUFFIXES_AND_RESOLUTIONS for more details about image resolution IDs.

        Parameters:
        id - the image ID
        isAlbum - whether the image is the cover of an album or a track
        Returns:
        a URL of the image with this ID with a width up to 1200px

      • getImagesFromSearchResult

        @Nonnull
public static java.util.List<Image> getImagesFromSearchResult​(@Nonnull
                                                              org.jsoup.nodes.Element searchResult)
        Get a list of images from a search result Element.

        This method will call getImagesFromImageUrl(String) using the first non null and non empty image URL found from the src attribute of img HTML elements, or an empty string if no valid image URL was found.

        Parameters:
        searchResult - a search result Element
        Returns:
        an unmodifiable list of Images, which is never null but can be empty, in the case where no valid image URL was found

      • getImagesFromImageUrl

        @Nonnull
public static java.util.List<Image> getImagesFromImageUrl​(@Nullable
                                                          java.lang.String imageUrl)
        Get all images which have resolutions preserving aspect ratio from an image URL.

        This method will remove the image ID and its extension from the end of the URL and then call getImagesFromImageBaseUrl(String).

        Parameters:
        imageUrl - the full URL of an image provided by Bandcamp, such as in its HTML code
        Returns:
        an unmodifiable list of Images, which is never null but can be empty, in the case where the image URL has been not extracted (and so is null or empty)

      • getImagesFromImageId

        @Nonnull
public static java.util.List<Image> getImagesFromImageId​(long id,
                                                         boolean isAlbum)
        Get all images which have resolutions preserving aspect ratio from an image ID.

        This method will call getImagesFromImageBaseUrl(String).

        Parameters:
        id - the id of an image provided by Bandcamp
        isAlbum - whether the image is the cover of an album
        Returns:
        an unmodifiable list of Images, which is never null but can be empty, in the case where the image ID has been not extracted (and so equal to 0)
